liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Lovely kick from Cleary goes up, is contested, falls to Luai who this time has a simple pass wide to Crichton who dives over in the corner. The Blues strike back! It's 16-16 - and Cleary nails the kick! The Blues lead by 2 points!
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: 66' TRY NEW SOUTH WALES!

children.content: Lovely kick from Cleary goes up, is contested, falls to Luai who this time has a simple pass wide to Crichton who dives over in the corner.
It's 16-16 - and Cleary nails the kick!

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Selwyn Cobbo slides across the line on his knees after avoiding two head-high tackles from Tedesco and Luai, after Brian To'o was taken out the defence by a wonderful pass by Reece Walsh as the Maroons probed down the right side. It's an excellent try from the two Broncos. And the kick isn't bad from the Cowboy Val Holmes on the sideline! The Maroons lead 16-12.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: 58' TRY MAROONS!

children.content: Selwyn Cobbo slides across the line on his knees after avoiding two head-high tackles from Tedesco and Luai, after Brian To'o was taken out the defence by a wonderful pass by Reece Walsh as the Maroons probed down the right side.
It's an excellent try from the two Broncos.
And the kick isn't bad from the Cowboy Val Holmes on the sideline!

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: There was a loose ball and that is a gift for Apisai Koroisau! There was an attempted offload from Val Holmes but the ball was knocked down ?and forward? possibly by Api Koroisau who then picked it up and scooted over the score unopposed. This will likely come back though. The try has been confirmed! That's extraordinary! The Maroons might have got a couple of decisions go their way in the first half, but the Blues have definitely seen their luck turn here. The kick is good and the Blues lead 12-10!
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: 44' Blues try!

children.content: There was a loose ball and that is a gift for Apisai Koroisau!

There was an attempted offload from Val Holmes but the ball was knocked down ?and forward? possibly by Api Koroisau who then picked it up and scooted over the score unopposed. This will likely come back though.
The Maroons might have got a couple of decisions go their way in the first half, but the Blues have definitely seen their luck turn here.
The kick is good and the Blues lead 12-10!
